            "question_type": "multiple_choice",
            "question": "What is the difference between a concept note and a work plan?",
            "options": [
              "A concept note is for getting stakeholders while a work plan is how this will be achieved",
              "A work plan is for getting stakeholders while a concept note is how this will be achieved",
              "They are the same."
            ],
            "correct_answer": "A concept note is for getting stakeholders while a work plan is how this will be achieved",
            "show_feedback": true,
            "feedback_correct": "Correct! The concept note is the initial document used to gain stakeholder buy-in. The work plan is the detailed roadmap for how you will achieve the approved idea.",
            "gridX": 0,
            "gridY": 0,
            "gridW": 12,
            "gridH": 3
          }
        },
        {
          "orderIndex": 1,
